'''Mary Elizabeth Atkins''' (born in [[London]]) was an [[England|English]] painter of landscape, interiors and flowers.

Atkins studied at the [[Slade School of Art|Slade School]] and exhibited at the [[Royal Academy]] and the [[New English Art Club]].

Her painting of the village of [[Chalford]] is in the collection of [[Leeds Art Gallery]] since 1927.<ref>[http://www.bbc.co.uk/arts/yourpaintings/paintings/chalford-gloucestershire-37497 ''Chalford, Gloucestershire'' by Mary Elizabeth Atkins], BBC - Your Paintings. Retrieved 2014-01-01.</ref>

